[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA heap-buffer-overflow was detected by AddressSanitizer while running the [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer` against the libexif codebase. The overflow occurs in the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `exif-data.c` at line [0m[1;36m213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, where a [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read via `memcpy` exceeds a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocated region. This vulnerability [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis classified as a heap-based buffer overflow.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue Type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The crash report identifies a multi-byte, heap-based buffer overflow triggered by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39man out-of-bounds read of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m immediately past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Crash Details  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  AddressSanitizer reports:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Location: `__asan_memcpy` called from `exif_data_load_data_entry`  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Read address: [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes beyond the allocated region [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • Allocation site: a `malloc` in the fuzzer driver during test execution  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Call Stack Highlights  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `__asan_memcpy`  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:531[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:984[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. `exif_data_new_from_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:159[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzzer entry point in `exif_from_data_fuzzer.[0m[1;92mcc:51[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The buffer overflow is detected during the processing of a fuzz-generated input[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby the EXIF data loader.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The offending `memcpy` attempts to read more bytes than were allocated for the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF data entry.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m simply wraps [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_new_from_data` and is not the direct cause.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code Areas for Investigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  To fully understand the issue, the following parts of the codebase should be [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreviewed:  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • `exif_data_load_data_entry` in `libexif/exif-data.c` around line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfocusing on how entry lengths are validated before copying.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • The functions `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data` in the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame file, which build on the data entry parsing logic.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • The buffer size calculations and any boundary checks applied to the EXIF data[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructures.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    • The test harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer.cc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm how input blobs are [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:1006[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1012[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1006[0m[39m:   [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1007[0m[39m:   [0m[39m * If we got an EXIF_TAG_MAKER_NOTE, try to interpret it. Some[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1008[0m[39m:   [0m[39m * cameras use pointers in the maker note tag that point to the[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1009[0m[39m:   [0m[39m * space between IFDs. Here is the only place where we have access[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1010[0m[39m:   [0m[39m * to that data.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1011[0m[39m:   [0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1012[0m[39m:   [0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d, fullds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:202[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m207[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff+s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The heap-buffer-overflow occurs in `exif_data_load_data_entry` when a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` reads past the end of the input buffer. Under normal EXIF parsing, the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode invokes:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, ds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, …[0m[1;39m)[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     so that the pointer `d` and length `size = ds-[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` stay in sync, and the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting two-stage bounds checks[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     prevent out-of-bounds reads.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - However, in the MakerNote branch [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d, fullds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`d` is passed as the raw input pointer [0m[1;39m([0m[39mincluding the [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-byte header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `size = [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfullds` is the original input length. Internally, `interpret_maker_note` eventually[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls back into `exif_data_load_data_content` → `exif_data_load_data_entry` with a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatched `d`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`size` context, so the `doff`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`s` checks are satisfied yet the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` can read past the true end of the allocated buffer.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The root cause is two-fold:[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m `exif_data_load_data_entry` uses separate checks that assume `size` always [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorresponds exactly to the bytes accessible at `d`. A non-unitary check allows edge[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcases to slip through when `d`[0m[35m/[0m[39m`size` are misaligned.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m The MakerNote invocation passes a different `[0m[1;39m([0m[39md, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pair than the rest [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof the parsing logic, breaking that invariant.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy Overview[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tighten the bounds validation in `exif_data_load_data_entry` to a single [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcombined check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`, which covers both `doff >= size` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `s > size - doff` in one atomic test. This eliminates any gap between the two [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Normalize the pointer/length context for MakerNote parsing. Two approaches [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mchoose one or both for defense in depth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Update the call site in `exif_data_load_data` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround the existing [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d, fullds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to pass `d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` and `ds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` instead of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe raw `[0m[1;39m([0m[39md, fullds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. This ensures MakerNote parsing sees exactly the same buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslice and length that the rest of EXIF parsing does.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. As an alternative or supplement, modify `[0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` itself to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjust its local pointer/size arguments before any call into [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand thus `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, e.g. subtract[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-byte header offset and reduce the length accordingly.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Modify exif_data_load_data_entry bounds check[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Replace lines [0m[1;36m198[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m207[0m[39m:[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       with:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Combined overflow check: ensure doff + s does not exceed buffer length[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms > [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                      doff + s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Rationale: a single check prevents any possible two-stage timing/logic gap [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand automatically covers both invalid offsets and invalid lengths.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Normalize MakerNote parsing context[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Option [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpreferred, minimal invasive[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - In `exif_data_load_data` at the call site:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Old:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d, fullds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m New:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Pass the same data‐pointer and length used by [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_content initially:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, fullds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - This change reestablishes the invariant that, whenever we hand a `[0m[1;39m([0m[39md, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pair into content/entry loaders, `d` points to the first byte of the [0m[1;36m0x002a[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtag and `size` is the remaining length.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     Option [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39min interpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - At the top of `[0m[1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data, const unsigned char [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m*d, unsigned int size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` insert:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           const unsigned char *base = d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           unsigned int   len  = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize >= [0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ? size - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m : [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m And use [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbase, len[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in any calls to exif_data_load_data_content[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - This self‐corrects any future mis‐invocations.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The combined check in `exif_data_load_data_entry` is strictly stronger than [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe previous two checks but does not alter valid code paths [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere `doff + s <= [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adjusting the MakerNote invocation does not alter the data loaded for valid [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMakerNote segments—it merely realigns the pointer and size to match the rest of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF parser.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external or fuzzing harness code is modified. All changes are internal to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libexif/exif-data.c`.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Side Effects & Mitigation[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Valid but malformed inputs that previously read exactly up to the end [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi.e., [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff+s == size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain allowed [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`<= size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The condition uses `>` so equality is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfine.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Logging calls remain unchanged, except that we now log a single consistent [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmessage for out‐of‐bounds.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Unit tests for MakerNote parsing and boundary conditions should be added to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcover:[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • A MakerNote tag whose offset + length exactly equals buffer size.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       • A MakerNote tag whose offset or length is out of range.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     This ensures no regression or unintended masking of errors.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. References & Similar Patterns[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The rewrite of multiple‐stage bounds checks into a single atomic `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moff + [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlen > bufsize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` pattern is already applied elsewhere in the code [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., IFD1 length[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks at lines [0m[1;36m986[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m995[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Aligning MakerNote parsing context with the main IFD parsing path maintains [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistency and prevents special‐case logic from drifting out of sync.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m[12/27/25 23:43:48][0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Prism Supervisor Routing: TeamStatus.EVALUATE -> TeamStatus.ANALYZE                  ]8;id=229455;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py\[2m__init__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=439885;file:///home/qqor/crete/packages/crete/framework/agent/services/prism/__init__.py#160\[2m160[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer–reported heap-buffer-overflow was observed inside libexif’s [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry function when a fuzzer invocation read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes past the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte allocation. The attempted patch consolidated two separate bounds [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks into a single arithmetic comparison of `doff + s` against `size` and [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madjusted an offset in the call to `interpret_maker_note`. When re-running the same [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer input against the patched library, the same out-of-bounds read recurred at a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslightly shifted source location, indicating the patch did not prevent the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arises during a fuzzing session of the exif_from_data_fuzzer. [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reports a multi-byte read overflow at exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:213[0m[39m inside [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, triggered by a call to `__asan_memcpy`. The buffer in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mquestion had been allocated with [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes, yet the code attempted to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstarting at the final byte of that allocation. The fuzzer log shows:[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m • A call chain from `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` through `exif_data_new_from_data` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m • The invalid read originates from copying metadata content when parsing a tag’s [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata entry.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m • Allocation size was [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes; the computed read offset exactly equaled the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation length, causing a zero-byte gap before the overflow.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt modified the code in exif-data.c around the entry‐loading logic. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mIt removed two separate checks:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m … return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand replaced them with:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms > [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff+s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAdditionally, the patch altered the call[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d, fullds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35minterpret_maker_note[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, d + [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, fullds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpresumably to adjust for a header offset in the maker-note segment.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer, the same ASan failure appeared. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcrash location shifted slightly to exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:207[0m[39m, but still inside [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`, indicating the combined guard did not block the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds memcpy. The new run log mirrors the original, with the same [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation size and identical shadow-memory layout at the overflow address.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mKey code areas for further investigation:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The calculation of `doff` and `s` that determines how much data is copied and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere it begins.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation size provided to `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` versus the range of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes accessed by memcpy.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any special cases in tag parsing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example, tags with zero length or very [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge length fields[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that might allow an overflow despite the guard.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The logic in `interpret_maker_note` and surrounding offset adjustments, since the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch also touched that function call but did not affect the failing branch.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA holistic review should trace how tag offsets and lengths are read from the input [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer, validated, and then used to allocate and copy memory, ensuring that every [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpath to `__asan_memcpy` is preceded by a correct bounds check.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [32mthumbnail offset [0m[32m([0m[32m%u[0m[32m)[0m[32m."[0m[39m, o[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m331[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m332[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m333[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo,ds,s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m334[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Bogus [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mthumbnail size [0m[32m([0m[32m%u[0m[32m)[0m[32m, max would be %u."[0m[39m, s, ds-o[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m335[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m336[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m337[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m338[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_mem_free [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->mem, data->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m339[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->data = exif_data_alloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m340[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m341[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdata->size = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m342[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m343[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m344[0m[39m:    [0m[39mdata->size = s;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m345[0m[39m:    [0m[39mmemcpy [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->data, d + o, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m346[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m347[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m348[0m[39m:#undef CHECK_REC[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m349[0m[39m:#define [0m[1;35mCHECK_REC[0m[1;39m([0m[39mi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m350[0m[39m:if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == ifd[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m351[0m[39m:    [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, \[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m352[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Recursive entry in IFD "[0m[39m   [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m353[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[32m"'%s' detected. Skipping..."[0m[39m,   [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m354[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_ifd_get_name [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m355[0m[39m:    [0m[39mbreak;  [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m356[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m   [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m357[0m[39m:if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->ifd[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m([0m[39mi[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m][0m[39m->count[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m358[0m[39m:    [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m359[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Attempt to load IFD "[0m[39m      [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m360[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[32m"'%s' multiple times detected. "[0m[39m        [0m[39m\[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:183[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m187[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:    [0m[39ms = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * entry->components;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m{[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m187[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:328[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m336[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m328[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity checks *[0m[35m/[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m329[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mo >= ds[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m330[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Bogus [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mthumbnail offset [0m[32m([0m[32m%u[0m[32m)[0m[32m."[0m[39m, o[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m331[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m332[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m333[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo,ds,s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m334[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Bogus [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32mthumbnail size [0m[32m([0m[32m%u[0m[32m)[0m[32m, max would be %u."[0m[39m, s, ds-o[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m335[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m336[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root-Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The core bug arises because the parsers use a *clamped* buffer length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor all entry‐bounds checks, yet the actual buffer in memory remains the *full* [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fullds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  For example, a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte EXIF segment is clamped to [0m[1;36m201[0m[39m bytes [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ds - [0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so `exif_data_load_data_entry` thinks it only has [0m[1;36m201[0m[39m bytes to validate[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst, even though the underlying data buffer is still [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes long.  This [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmismatch lets a malicious or malformed tag slip past the guard and then perform a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` that reads past the real end of the *entry* allocation.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additionally, the single combined check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` uses the wrong [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“size” [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe clamped length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and does not employ the proven `[0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo,ds,s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpattern used elsewhere [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., thumbnail[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, nor does it robustly check for [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiplication overflow when computing `s`.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Overall Strategy[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Reintroduce two distinct sizes throughout the parsing pipeline:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **total_size** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fullds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – the true byte length of the EXIF data segment [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mminus the initial header if appropriate[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **clamp_size** [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – a safety cap [0m[1;39m([0m[39m≤[0m[1;36m0xFFFE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m used only to prevent [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mextremely large or corrupt IFD counts from causing integer overflow in offset [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloops.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Ensure that:[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - All *IFD-count* and *offset arithmetic* loops use **clamp_size** to remain [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithin the [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m KiB JPEG-APP1 limit.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Every **memcpy** or buffer read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mespecially in `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses **total_size** in a `CHECKOVERFLOW` guard, preventing any out-of-bounds access[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst the real allocation.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Strengthen the size‐multiplication guard for the number of components × [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat_size by switching to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit arithmetic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor the existing `CHECKOVERFLOW` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midiom[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to make overflow impossible.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. In `exif-data.c` where the APP1 length is read:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Keep `fullds = ds;`[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Introduce a new local `clamp_size = [0m[1;35mMIN[0m[1;39m([0m[39mds, [0m[1;36m0xFFFE[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Do **not** overwrite `ds` with the clamp – keep `ds` always equal to the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreal length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fullds`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Change the call into `[0m[1;35mexif_data_load_data_content[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace the current `d+[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, ds-[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m` with two arguments: `d+[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, clamp_size-[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfullds-[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Update the signature of `exif_data_load_data_content` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand internal calls[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto accept both `clamp_size` and `total_size`.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. In `exif_data_load_data_content`:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Use **clamp_size** exclusively for the IFD‐entry loop limit and offset [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation that prevents unreasonably large loops.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - When invoking `exif_data_load_data_entry`, pass both the pointer to the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata buffer and the two size parameters.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. In `exif_data_load_data_entry`:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Replace the current guard[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff + [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms > [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        with the established macro:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff, total_size, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Use a [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit multiplication check [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor `CHECKOVERFLOW`‐style[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for `s = [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat_size * components` to catch any wraparound:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          uint64_t tmp = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mformat_size * components;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtmp == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m || tmp > UINT_MAX[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m tmp;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. In the thumbnail loader [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_thumbnail`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, confirm it already[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses:[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mCHECKOVERFLOW[0m[1;39m([0m[39mo, ds, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      – ensure that `ds` here is the “true” buffer length.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Separation of concerns**: By splitting “clamped” from “real” size, we [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmaintain the original rationale for the [0m[1;36m0xFFFE[0m[39m cap [0m[1;39m([0m[39mprotect against absurd counts[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhile always comparing actual copy operations against the real allocation length.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Reusing tested patterns**: Adopting the existing `CHECKOVERFLOW` macro [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensures consistency with other parts of the code [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthumbnail, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that were [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready ASan-clean.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Preserves functionality**: All existing IFD parsing loops and maker‐note [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic remain intact. We have only enriched the bounds checking, not removed any [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic or changed semantics.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **No harness or external change**: We modify only `libexif/exif-data.c` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mkeep the public API of `exif_data_load_data_content` internal. Fuzzing harnesses, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests, and external libraries are untouched.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Multiplication overflow guard**: Strengthening the component‐size check [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevents future wraparound bugs for pathological `component × format_size` [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcombinations.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Potential Side-Effects and Mitigations[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changing the signature of `exif_data_load_data_content` and internal calls is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma refactoring risk, but all call sites are within one compilation unit. A single [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch will update both declaration and all invocations.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Clamping no longer reduces the real `ds` used in parsing; however, since we [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill use `clamp_size` for loop/IFD count protection, untrusted inputs cannot [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtrigger excessively large IFD loops.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stricter multiplication‐overflow guard could reject some extremely large [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mbut valid?[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m tags; this is desired for safety, and any spec-compliant image beyond [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UINT_MAX` components would already be unreasonably large.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduce two size variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`clamp_size` ≤ [0m[1;36m0xFFFE[0m[39m and true `total_size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Propagate `total_size` into every memcpy guard via `CHECKOVERFLOW`,  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Strengthen component‐size multiplication checks,  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Leave harness, tests, and utilities untouched.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This strategy directly prevents the previously observed heap-buffer-overflow [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout altering legitimate parsing behavior.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
